The problem provides you a .txt file where you can get a encrypted text.
1.At first go to terminal, then  Follow what showed below:
┌──(kali㉿kali)-[~]
└─$ ls                   
Desktop  Documents  Downloads  Music  Pictures  Public  Templates  Videos                                                                                                                                                                     
┌──(kali㉿kali)-[~]
└─$ cd ~/Downloads                                                                                                                                                                   
┌──(kali㉿kali)-[~/Downloads]
└─$ ls
enc_flag                                                                                                                                                                    
┌──(kali㉿kali)-[~/Downloads]
└─$ open enc_flag                                                                                                                                                                           
┌──(kali㉿kali)-[~/Downloads]
└─$ open enc_flag                                                                                                                                                                    
┌──(kali㉿kali)-[~/Downloads]
└─$ base64 -d enc_flag
b'd3BqdkpBTXtqaGx6aHlfazNqeTl3YTNrXzg5MGsyMzc5fQ=='
2. Here as u can see we got a decrypted text. Copy this and go to < https://www.base64decode.org/ > to decode it again.
3.Here you will find something like wpjvJAM{jhlzhy_k3jy9wa3k_890k2379}.
4. Then,let us jump into < https://www.dcode.fr/caesar-cipher > , here i searched rot13 in the search bar ,used Caesar Cipher (rot13, rot) to decode. You can use other decoding tools too.
5. Thus you will get your flag from this decryption .Problem solved.
